A vintage 1970s technical illustration showing a large filing cabinet being dramatically compressed by a massive industrial vice or hydraulic press, with papers and folders visibly compacting inside. The cabinet transforms from an oversized, bloated wooden unit on the left to a sleek, compact metal version on the right. Warm sepia and burnt orange tones dominate, with crosshatching details and aged paper texture throughout. Small measurement rulers and percentage graphs float around the scene in a retro infographic style. The background features faded blueprint grid paper with coffee stains at the edges.
